The paper deals with geometric algorithms and the evaluation of algebraic expressions, which are common topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The analysis of the efficacy of arithmetic filters also involves probability theory, which is relevant to stochastic systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential errors introduced by rounded arithmetic, which is a concern in scientific computing (cs.SC) and data structures (cs.DS).
